Podcast!</a></BLOCKQUOTE>

        <LI><FONT SIZE="+1"><strong><A HREF="http://forums.oldradio.net/">Old-Time Radio Forums!</A></strong></FONT>
        <BLOCKQUOTE>Bulletin Boards for Old-Time Radio Programs, including The Shadow, Suspense, I Love a Mystery, Fibber McGee and Molly, and more! Free registration, great information! Newly upgraded, easy to use, with boards targeted to specific programs or genres!</BLOCKQUOTE>

        <LI><FONT SIZE="+1"><strong><A HREF="http://blogs.oldradio.net/">Nostalgic Rumblings</A></strong></FONT>
        <BLOCKQUOTE>News and views about Old-Time Radio, Nostalgic and Contemporary Television, pointers to news stories from around the Internet, as well as the occasional book review, convention photo spread, or opinion piece by the Webmaster and long-time Old-Time Radio collector!</BLOCKQUOTE>

        <LI><FONT SIZE="+1"><strong><A HREF="http://www.otrdigest.com/">The Internet OTR Digest!</A></strong></FONT>
        <BLOCKQUOTE>The oldest, largest, and best daily dose of Old-Time 
Radio talk on the planet, delivered conveniently to your email box every day! This list (currently available in Digest format only) was started on September 14th, 1994 by Lou Genco, and has been published continuously <em>ever since,</em> giving the thousands of subscribers access to unparalleled amounts of on-topic information! It's a large free-form venue for discussing Old-Time Radio with thousands of other people. Almost <em>any</em> topic related to OTR is welcomed on this list!</BLOCKQUOTE>


</UL>

